reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Dr. Johnson explains complex concepts clearly. Her labs are challenging but enlightening.

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Brilliant instructor! Prof. Chen's passion for coding is contagious. Best CS class I've taken.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Decent lectures, but exams are much harder than the material covered in class.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Prof. Lee is patient and willing to help. His office hours are incredibly useful.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Engaging lectures and fascinating experiments. Dr. Martinez is a true expert in her field.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Monotonous lectures. Relies too heavily on memorization rather than critical thinking.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Challenging course, but Dr. Brown's enthusiasm makes it enjoyable. Great lab sessions.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Knowledgeable, but sometimes unclear in his expectations for assignments.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Thought-provoking discussions and relevant case studies. Dr. Kowalski is inspirational.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Clear explanations of complex economic theories. Prof. Garcia uses great real-world examples.

reviews.subject: Neuroscience
reviews.review: Cutting-edge research incorporated into lectures. Dr. Patel is at the top of her field.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Extensive knowledge, but lectures can be dry. More interactive elements would help.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Passionate about the subject. Field trips are a highlight of Dr. Schmidt's course.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Often goes off on tangents. Grading seems arbitrary and feedback is minimal.

reviews.subject: Genetics
reviews.review: Exceptional at breaking down complex genetic concepts. Dr. Lee's research is fascinating.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Knowledgeable but biased in presentations. Encourages debate, which is good.

reviews.subject: Astrophysics
reviews.review: Challenging material, but Dr. Chen's enthusiasm is infectious. Star-gazing sessions are amazing.

reviews.subject: Marketing
reviews.review: Good real-world experience, but course structure could be improved.

reviews.subject: Linguistics
reviews.review: Fascinating course content. Dr. Lopez makes language study exciting and relevant.

reviews.subject: Civil Engineering
reviews.review: Practical approach to teaching. Prof. Thompson's industry connections are valuable.

reviews.subject: Quantum Physics
reviews.review: Brilliant mind. Dr. Tanaka somehow makes quantum physics understandable and exciting.

reviews.subject: Business Ethics
reviews.review: Outdated case studies. Prof. Green seems disinterested in student opinions.

reviews.subject: International Relations
reviews.review: Insightful discussions on global issues. Dr. Ali brings a wealth of experience to the class.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: Clear explanations, but pacing is too fast. More practice problems would be helpful.

reviews.subject: Organic Chemistry
reviews.review: Tough course, but Dr. Miller is always available to help. His molecular models are fantastic.

reviews.subject: Film Studies
reviews.review: Passionate and knowledgeable. Prof. Rodriguez's analysis of films is eye-opening.

reviews.subject: Mechanical Engineering
reviews.review: Solid theoretical knowledge, but could use more practical applications in class.

reviews.subject: Gender Studies
reviews.review: Thought-provoking lectures. Prof. Johnson creates a safe space for open discussions.

reviews.subject: Artificial Intelligence
reviews.review: Cutting-edge course content. Dr. Gupta's projects are challenging and rewarding.

reviews.subject: Music Theory
reviews.review: Excellent at explaining complex musical concepts. Prof. Larsson's ear training sessions are particularly helpful.
